note._content: Is there a date here on White's fascade?1912?
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: New tram  tracks?New Spit-to-Manly Tram opened 1911.Original horse-drawn,then steam tram ran down the Corso,then North Steyne,Carlton St.,Pittwater Road to Manly Lagoon
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: North-east corner of Corso and Whistler St. was redeveloped c1913-14 for Castle Vernon Flats with shops on ground floor.First listed in Sands Directory 1915 ie completed by late 1914.Still standing and heritage listed with rest of The Corso.
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: Purves Bakery built 1898(see date on parapet)
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: Chinese lanterns?If photo is after 1912,then perhaps taken during Manly's famed Venetian Carnival held in summer and centred on Manly Cove and The Corso.
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: No Manly War Memorial,unveiled by Governor-General in 1916(the first in Australia?),so photo taken no later than 1915.
note.author: 39165494@N06

note._content: Multiple tram lines suggest date after Spit-to-Manly tram route opened in 1911.
note.author: 39165494@N06
